## Phase 5 — Remediate

- Patch the vulnerability.
- Add a regression test that proves the vulnerability cannot recur.
- Update the threat model in `docs/architecture.md` (or equivalent) if
  the breach exposed a structural gap.
- If the breach involved a subprocessor, escalate to the vendor and
  reassess their entry in [`subprocessors.md`](subprocessors.md).

## Phase 6 — Postmortem (within 7 days of containment)

- Blameless postmortem doc (`[fill in: where postmortems live in your
  project — e.g., docs/runbooks/postmortems/<date>-<slug>.md]`).
- Root cause + contributing factors + timeline + lessons.
- Action items with owners + due dates.
- Update `CLAUDE.md` "Lessons Learned" if a future contributor needs to
  inherit a behavioral change (e.g., a check that gets added to the
  security checklist).

